response:
I have everything. The diagnosis is clear. Now I'll make all three changes: fix the SCSS, amend AP-066 in the anti-patterns catalog, and add the nav identity priority rule to `branding.md`.

---

## Diagnosis

The bug is a **three-layer flex compression failure** in `Navigation.module.scss`:

1. **`.logo` has `flex-shrink: 0`** — correct intent, but it's not enough on its own.
2. **`.logo` has no `min-width`** — when the flex container overflows, the browser's layout engine is still allowed to solve the overflow by wrapping the *contents* of `.logo` even though the element itself can't shrink, because `white-space: nowrap` is on `.logoText` (a child span) rather than on the anchor itself. If the anchor has no `min-width`, any gap between the intrinsic width and what the browser will commit to can cause a re-layout.
3. **`.links` has `min-width: 0`** (correct, to allow the tagline to yield), but there's no corresponding **`min-width: max-content`** or explicit `min-width` on `.logo` to signal to the flex container that this child has an inviolable floor.
4. The deepest issue: `white-space: nowrap` is on `.logoText` but **not on `.logo` (the anchor itself)**. The anchor is a flex item. If the flex algorithm ever considers wrapping inside the anchor element before the `nowrap` on the inner span fires, the logo mark and text could split onto two lines — the `nowrap` only protects the span's text from line-breaking, not from the mark and text wrapping relative to each other if the gap between them compresses.

## Root Cause

**AP-066: Unconstrained Flex Compression Breaking Identity Text.** The `.logo` flex item was protected with `flex-shrink: 0` but not with `min-width: max-content`, leaving the browser's overflow-solving algorithm free to wrap the icon+text pair when the container hits critical width. The existing AP-066 entry in the catalog already names this pattern but its "correct alternative" section didn't enumerate the full three-property combination (`flex-shrink: 0` + `min-width: max-content` + `white-space: nowrap` on the container itself).

---

## Fix

Three files change: the SCSS (the actual bug fix), `docs/design-anti-patterns.md` (amend AP-066 with the complete canonical fix pattern), and `docs/design/branding.md` (codify the nav identity priority rule).

### 1. `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`

```scss
@use '../../../styles' as *;

.nav {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: var(--portfolio-z-sticky);
  background-color: var(--portfolio-surface-terra-subtle);
  box-shadow: 0 4px 12px -4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);

  &::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 10px;
    transform: translateY(100%);
    backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
}

.navInner {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  // gap instead of relying on child margins — keeps logo and links cleanly separated
  gap: var(--portfolio-spacer-2x);
  max-width: $elan-container-wide;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-2x);

  @media #{$elan-mq-sm} {
    padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-4x);
  }
}

.logo {
  // ─── IDENTITY LOCK (AP-066) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
  // "Yilan Gao" is a core identity line. It must NEVER wrap to two lines,
  // shrink, or collapse under any flex pressure. This is a brand hard rule
  // (branding.md §10). Three properties work together:
  //   1. flex-shrink: 0      — prevents the item from shrinking in the flex row
  //   2. min-width: max-content — sets the item's floor to its intrinsic width,
  //                              blocking the browser from considering any
  //                              sub-intrinsic layout solution
  //   3. white-space: nowrap — on this anchor (not just the child span) so the
  //                            flex algorithm never splits the mark from the text
  // The tagline in .links absorbs all remaining squeeze by wrapping instead.
  // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: $portfolio-spacer-0-5x;
  text-decoration: none;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  min-width: max-content;
  white-space: nowrap;
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    .logoMark {
      background-color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }

    .logoText {
      color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }
  }
}

.logoMark {
  display: inline-block;
  height: calc($portfolio-type-2xl * 1.2);
  aspect-ratio: 1;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  background-color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  mask-image: url('/images/yg-logo.svg');
  mask-size: contain;
  mask-repeat: no-repeat;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.logoText {
  font-family: $portfolio-font-serif;
  font-size: $portfolio-type-2xl;
  font-weight: $portfolio-weight-regular;
  line-height: $portfolio-leading-snug;
  color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  letter-spacing: $portfolio-tracking-tight;
  white-space: nowrap;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.links {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--portfolio-spacer-3x);
  // The tagline is the soft edge of the nav. min-width: 0 lets it compress
  // freely so any overflow is resolved here, never in .logo.
  min-width: 0;
  flex-shrink: 1;
}

.link {
  font-family: var(--portfolio-font-sans);
  font-size: var(--portfolio-type-sm);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-regular);
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  text-decoration: none;
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  }
}

.linkActive {
  color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-medium);
}

.tagline {
  @include body-sm;
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  // The tagline is the designated yield point in the nav row. It is allowed
  // to wrap to two lines under squeeze — that is its correct behavior.
  // It must never wrap beyond two lines (line-clamp: 2).
  min-width: 0;
  text-align: right;
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 2;
  line-clamp: 2;
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

**What changed and why:**

| Change | Location | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Added `min-width: max-content` | `.logo` | Sets an inviolable floor at the element's intrinsic rendered width. The flex algorithm cannot solve an overflow constraint by shrinking this item below its natural size. |
| Moved `white-space: nowrap` up to `.logo` (anchor) | `.logo` | Was only on `.logoText` (inner span). The anchor itself needs `nowrap` so the flex algorithm never considers wrapping the mark and text relative to each other. |
| Added `gap` to `.navInner` | `.navInner` | Explicit gap between logo and links instead of implicit margin. Prevents the gap from being squeezed away before `min-width` kicks in. |
| Added `flex-shrink: 1` explicitly | `.links` | Makes explicit which side absorbs the squeeze — `.links` grows/shrinks, `.logo` never shrinks. |

